  \"metadata\": {},\n","      \"source\": [\n","        \"---\\n\",\n","        \"\\n\",\n","        \"# 1. Variables and Data Types {#variables-and-data-types}\\n\",\n","        \"\\n\",\n","        \"## Concept Explanation\\n\",\n","        \"\\n\",\n","        \"A **variable** is a container for storing data values. Python automatically detects the data type based on the value assigned.\\n\",\n","        \"\\n\",\n","        \"### Main Data Types:\\n\",\n","        \"- **int**: Integer (whole numbers)\\n\",\n","        \"- **float**: Floating-point numbers (decimals)\\n\",\n","        \"- **str**: Strings (text)\\n\",\n","        \"- **bool**: Boolean (True/False)\\n\",\n","        \"- **list**: Collection of items\\n\",\n","        \"- **tuple**: Immutable collection\\n\",\n","        \"- **dict**: Key-value pairs\\n\",\n","        \"- **set**: Unique items\"\n","      ]\n","    },\n","    {\n","      \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n","      \"execution_count\": null,\n","      \"metadata\": {},\n","      \"outputs\": [],\n","      \"source\": [\n","        \"# Example 1: Creating Variables and Checking Data Types\\n\",\n","        \"name = \\\"Alice\\\"          # String variable\\n\",\n","        \"age = 25               # Integer variable\\n\",\n","        \"height = 5.6           # Float variable\\n\",\n","        \"is_student = True      # Boolean variable\\n\",\n","        \"\\n\",\n","        \"print(\\\"Variable Values and Their Types:\\\")\\n\",\n","        \"print(f\\\"Name: {name}, Type: {type(name)}\\\")\\n\",\n","        \"print(f\\\"Age: {age}, Type: {type(age)}\\\")\\n\",\n","        \"print(f\\\"Height: {height}, Type: {type(height)}\\\")\\n\",\n","        \"print(f\\\"Is Student: {is_student}, Type: {type(is_student)}\\\")\"\n","      ]\n","    },\n","    {\n","      \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n","      \"metadata\": {},\n","      \"source\": [\n","        \"### Output Explanation:\\n\",\n","        \"The `type()` function returns the data type of a variable. Notice how Python automatically assigned the correct type based on the value we provided.\"\n","      ]\n","    },\n","    {\n","      \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n","      \"execution_count\": null,\n","      \"metadata\": {},\n","      \"outputs\": [],\n","      \"source\": [\n","        \"# Example 2: Variable Assignment and Reassignment\\n\",\n","        \"count = 10\\n\",\n","        \"print(f\\\"Initial count: {count}\\\")\\n\",\n","        \"\\n\",\n","        \"count = 20  # Reassigning the variable\\n\",\n","        \"print(f\\\"Updated count: {count}\\\")\\n\",\n","        \"\\n\",\n","        \"# Multiple assignment\\n\",\n","        \"x, y, z = 1, 2, 3\\n\",\n","        \"print(f\\\"\\\\nMultiple Assignment: x={x}, y={y}, z={z}\\\")\"\n","      ]\n","    },\n","    {\n","      \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n","      \"metadata\": {},\n","      \"source\": [\n","        \"---\\n\",\n","        \"\\n\",\n","        \"# 2. Numbers and Arithmetic Operations {#numbers-and-arithmetic-operations}\\n\",\n","        \"\\n\",\n","        \"## Concept Explanation\\n\",\n","        \"\\n\",\n","        \"Python supports various arithmetic operations: addition (+), subtraction (-), multiplication (*), division (/), floor division (//), modulus (%), and exponentiation (**).\"\n","      ]\n","    },\n","    {\n","      \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n","      \"execution_count\": null,\n","      \"metadata\": {},\n","      \"outputs\": [],\n","      \"source\": [\n","        \"# Example 1: Basic Arithmetic Operations\\n\",\n","        \"a = 15\\n\",\n","        \"b = 4\\n\",\n","        \"\\n\",\n","        \"print(\\\"Arithmetic Operations:\\\")\\n\",\n","        \"print(f\\\"Addition: {a} + {b} = {a + b}\\\")\\n\",\n","        \"print(f\\\"Subtraction: {a} - {b} = {a - b}\\\")\\n\",\n","        \"print(f\\\"Multiplication: {a} * {b} = {a * b}\\\")\\n\",\n","        \"print(f\\\"Division: {a} / {b} = {a / b}\\\")\\n\",\n","        \"print(f\\\"Floor Division: {a} // {b} = {a // b}\\\")\\n\",\n","        \"print(f\\\"Modulus (Remainder): {a} % {b} = {a % b}\\\")\\n\",\n","        \"print(f\\\"Exponentiation: {a} ** {b} = {a ** b}\\\")\"\n","      ]\n","    },\n","    {\n","      \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n","      \"metadata\": {},\n","      \"source\": [\n","        \"### Output Explanation:\\n\",\n","        \"- **Division (/)** always returns a float, even if both numbers are integers\\n\",\n","        \"- **Floor Division (//)** returns an integer (rounds down)\\n\",\n","        \"- **Modulus (%)** returns the remainder\\n\",\n","        \"- **Exponentiation (**)** raises to a power\"\n","      ]\n","    },\n","    {\n","      \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n","      \"execution_count\": null,\n","      \"metadata\": {},\n","      \"outputs\": [],\n","      \"source\": [\n","        \"# Example 2: Order of Operations (PEMDAS)\\n\",\n","        \"result1 = 10 + 5 * 2\\n\",\n","        \"result2 = (10 + 5) * 2\\n\",\n","        \"\\n\",\n","        \"print(\\\"Order of Operations:\\\")\\n\",\n","        \"print(f\\\"10 + 5 * 2 = {result1}  (Multiplication first)\\\")\\n\",\n","        \"print(f\\\"(10 + 5) * 2 = {result2}  (Parentheses first)\\\")\"\n","      ]\n","    },\n","    {\n","      \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n","      \"execution_count\": null,\n","      \"metadata\": {},\n","      \"outputs\": [],\n","      \"source\": [\n","        \"# Example 3: Augmented Assignment Operators\\n\",\n","        \"x = 10\\n\",\n","        \"print(f\\\"Initial value: x = {x}\\\")\\n\",\n","        \"\\n\",\n","        \"x += 5  # Same as x = x + 5\\n\",\n","        \"print(f\\\"After x += 5: x = {x}\\\")\\n\",\n","        \"\\n\",\n","        \"x -= 3  # Same as x = x - 3\\n\",\n","        \"print(f\\\"After x -= 3: x = {x}\\\")\\n\",\n","        \"\\n\",\n","        \"x *= 2  # Same as x = x * 2\\n\",\n","        \"print(f\\\"After x *= 2: x = {x}\\\")\\n\",\n","        \"\\n\",\n","        \"x //= 4  # Same as x = x // 4\\n\",\n","     